  • Constructor Details

    • BoundingBox3D

      public BoundingBox3D(float minX, float minY, float minZ, float maxX, float maxY, float maxZ)
      Create a new BoundingBox3D (rectangle shaped) to manage it in your code.
      Parameters:
      minX - the X-Position with a different name
      minY - the Y-Position with a different name
      minZ - the Z-Position with a different name
      maxX - the end X-Position of the Object (minX + width)
      maxY - the end Y-Position of the Object (minY + height)
      maxZ - the end Z-Position of the Object (minZ + depth)

    • BoundingBox3D

      public BoundingBox3D(float xPos, float yPos, float zPos, float diameter)
      Create a new BoundingBox3D (shaped like a sphere) to manage it in your code.
      Parameters:
      xPos - center X-Position of the sphere
      yPos - center Y-Position of the sphere
      zPos - center Z-Position of the sphere
      diameter - diameter of the sphere
